reviews.review: I went in with no expectations. Didn't overthink or over analyze, I simply enjoyed the ending of a story I have loved for 39 long years. I loved this movie. Captured the magical feeling I had as a child. Plus my daughter loved it too and watching her it felt like a whole new generation discovering the magic. What a thrill.

I think J.J. and the team did an awesome job of finishing the saga. There were so many loose ends, managing to put it all together and being completely fresh would have been next to impossible. Instead, they paid respect to the trilogy, had a perfect storyline, and made an awesome movie. Loved every minute....
Excellent film to closeout the saga. Goes a long way to fix the train wreck that Rian Johnson made with the last film

Movie was pretty good.  I felt like the director spent the first half of the movie cleaning up mess The Last Jedi left behind.  Once we got past all of that the second half of the movie was fantastic.  If the whole movie was as good as the second half this would have been a five star effort.  Indeed I have more respect for JJ Abrams now watching him repair all the damage caused by the previous director.  He did a good job with what the hand he was dealt.

Derek Connolly, Colin Trevorrow, J.J. Adams & Chris Terrio took the garbage story line from the previous Star Wars movie and did a surprisingly good job straightening out the mess by patching plot holes and going back to the basics. The result was an exceptionally good movie with a sensible plot, great screenplay and solid conclusion to the most recent Star Wars saga. Bravo!
Okay. Wrapped up, what turns out to be a completely unnecessary trilogy.
After a let-down that Episode VIII has been, this movie really made me feel Star Wars again. The good in this movie outshines the bad in this movie and makes a good ending to a beautiful story!
